    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-content"><h1>MCW Cancer Passport Registry</h1><p>Join a research registry at the Medical College of Wisconsin Cancer Center that helps match people with cancer to studies and trials—safely, securely, and on your terms.</p><a href="#contact" class="cta-button">Join the Registry</a></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Purpose Section -->
    <section id="purpose">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our Purpose</h2><div class="purpose-grid"><div class="purpose-card"><h3>Open the Door to Research</h3><p>The registry creates a secure, research-ready way for people with cancer and cancer survivors to share key health information so researchers can quickly identify relevant studies and trials.</p></div><div class="purpose-card"><h3>Faster, Fairer Access</h3><p>With standardized data and advance consent, MCW investigators can shorten the time from protocol approval to first-patient-in—broadening access to opportunities across cancer types and stages.</p></div><div class="purpose-card"><h3>Built for Trust</h3><p>Participation is voluntary, takes ~15–20 minutes for the required steps, and uses HIPAA-compliant safeguards with explicit consent and the right to withdraw at any time.</p></div></div>
    </section>

    <!-- About Section -->
    <section id="about">
        <h2 class="section-title">About the Registry</h2><div class="about-content"><p>The MCW Cancer Passport Registry is an observational research registry. It does not involve experimental drugs or procedures; instead it securely brings together key information you choose to share—like diagnosis details, surveys, and a secure connection to your electronic health records—to help researchers match you to relevant studies and trials.</p><p>What we collect:</p><ul><li>Basic information and contact preferences</li><li>Diagnosis and treatment details (from your medical records via a participant-mediated connection)</li><li>Quality-of-life surveys (EORTC QLQ-C30)</li><li>Optional modules, such as connecting a wearable device</li></ul><p>How it works:</p><ul><li>Review and sign a short electronic consent</li><li>Complete required baseline steps (~15–20 minutes total)</li><li>Optionally connect a wearable and/or opt-in to future sub-studies</li><li>We may re-contact you about IRB-approved opportunities that fit your profile</li></ul><div class="video-container"><iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1126252491?h=0&title=0&byline=0&portrait=0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen title="MCW Cancer Passport Registry Video"></iframe></div></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Eligibility Section -->
    <section id="eligibility">
        <h2 class="section-title">Eligibility</h2><div class="eligibility-content"><p>You can join if all of the following are true:</p><ul class="eligibility-list"><li>You are a current or former cancer patient (survivor).</li><li>You are age 18 or older and live in the United States.</li><li>You can give consent to participate.</li></ul><p><strong>You cannot join</strong> if any of the following apply:</p><ul class="eligibility-list"><li>You live outside of the United States.</li><li>You are unable to provide consent.</li><li>You are currently incarcerated.</li></ul></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Team Section -->
    <section id="team">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our Research Team</h2><div class="team-grid"><div class="team-member"><div class="team-member-photo">PI</div><h3>MCW Site Principal Investigator</h3><p>Leads the registry at MCW and oversees participant safety, data quality, and IRB compliance.</p></div><div class="team-member"><div class="team-member-photo">RC</div><h3>Research Coordinator</h3><p>Guides you through consent and enrollment, answers questions, and supports follow-up.</p></div><div class="team-member"><div class="team-member-photo">DA</div><h3>Data Analyst</h3><p>Ensures your data are harmonized and research-ready while protecting confidentiality.</p></div><div class="team-member"><div class="team-member-photo">CS</div><h3>Clinical Specialist</h3><p>Connects registry activities with your clinical care team when needed.</p></div></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Privacy & Ethics Section -->
    <section id="privacy">
        <h2 class="section-title">Privacy & Ethics</h2><div class="privacy-content"><p style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:2rem;">Your privacy and the ethical use of your data are our highest priorities.</p><div class="privacy-grid"><div class="privacy-item"><h3>IRB Oversight</h3><p>The registry is conducted under Institutional Review Board (IRB) oversight; all participant materials and amendments are IRB-approved before use.</p></div><div class="privacy-item"><h3>HIPAA-Compliant Safeguards</h3><p>Data are collected and stored using HIPAA-compliant security controls, including encryption in transit and at rest, role-based access, and audit logs.</p></div><div class="privacy-item"><h3>Participant Control</h3><p>You choose what to share, can withdraw at any time, and we only share coded data with qualified researchers unless you explicitly authorize contact for a specific study.</p></div><div class="privacy-item"><h3>De-identification & Governance</h3><p>When data are shared for research, direct identifiers are removed; all data sharing follows local governance and IRB approvals.</p></div></div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section id="faq">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="faq-container"><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">What is the MCW Cancer Passport Registry?</div><div class="faq-answer"><p>An observational registry that securely gathers information from people with cancer and cancer survivors to help identify relevant clinical trials and research studies more efficiently.</p></div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">Does joining affect my care?</div><div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Participation is voluntary and does not affect your clinical care. You may withdraw at any time.</p></div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">How long does enrollment take?</div><div class="faq-answer"><p>Most people complete the required steps in about 15–20 minutes (eConsent, a brief baseline survey set, and a secure medical-record connection). Optional modules may add a few minutes.</p></div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">What information is shared with researchers?</div><div class="faq-answer"><p>We share coded (de-identified) data for research uses under IRB oversight. Your name and contact details are only shared if you explicitly authorize contact for a specific study.</p></div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">Can I be in this registry and a clinical trial at the same time?</div><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. This registry does not prevent participation in other research. Individual trials have their own rules that your care team will review with you.</p></div></div><div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question">How will you contact me later?</div><div class="faq-answer"><p>We may re-contact you electronically about IRB-approved opportunities or to confirm your consent preferences. You control whether to proceed.</p></div></div></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact Section -->
    <section id="contact">
